    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72113/485</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GSU1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.03 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2051. For War Trade Board from <persName>Owen</persName>:<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d306fn1">
                        <persName>William H. Owen</persName>, of the Bureau of Foreign Agents, War
                        Trade Board.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Following from <hi rend="italic">Deutscher Reichsanzeiger</hi>, Berlin, March 11,
                    1918: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Official order regarding liquidation of American enterprises of March 4,
                            1918, on ground of article 12, paragraph 2, of act relating to
                            liquidation of British enterprises of 31st July 1916 (<hi rend="italic"
                                >Reichs-Gesetzblatt</hi>, p. 871), following is enacted: <list>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article</hi> 1. Regulations of act
                                    regarding liquidation of British enterprises of 31st July 1916
                                    are declared in the way of reprisal as applicable to
                                    enterprises, whose capital belongs predominantly to citizens of
                                    United States of America, or which are managed or controlled
                                    from the territory of the United States of America, or which
                                    were until the outbreak of the war managed or controlled
                                    therefrom, as well as to the interests of citizens of the United
                                    States of America in such enterprises.</item>
                                <pb facs="0374" n="290" xml:id="pg_290"/>
                                <item>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Art</hi>. 2. This order goes into effect
                                    the day of announcement. Berlin, March 4, 1918, signed
                                        <persName>Freiherr von Stein</persName>, representing
                                    Imperial Chancellor.</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>For act of 31st July, 1916, see <hi rend="italic">Kriegs-Notgesetze</hi>,
                    Library, Department of State.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Legation</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
